column5: Hello kids......  I got a question for the computer literate folk........  I always like to clear all my temporary internet files before I shut down.  For some reason there are a few I cant get rid of.  They appear to be "administrative" cookies and are stuck like glue when I try to delete them.  Any suggestions on how to get rid of them?? Running Windows XP.  Thanks for any info.....  Meely
http://www.piriform.com/ccleaner   amazing set of tools.Been using it for years.
If they are peanut butter I am willing to help...  What Mercman said.

If you run Firefox you should be able to remove regular cookies using ctrl+shift+P or go to "Tools" click on clear history. Just make sure you have a checkmark beside "Cookies".  If they are super cookies (LSO's) then you can get an add-on for Firefox to remove them.  The add-on is called "Better Privacy". When removing super cookies make sure you look at them,then pick the ones you want to remove. You can remove them all (remove all LSO's) or one by one by highlighting the LSO then click on "remove LSO". The main thing is know what you want to remove and what you want to keep.  Some games use LSO's for settings or data.  Tom
Just give them to this guy.
